# Redis Usage Standards

## Key naming — always follow the canonical pattern from DATABASE_SCHEMA.md

Every Redis key must include `org_id` as the second segment for multi-tenant isolation.

```text
Pattern:          {prefix}:{org_id}:{discriminator}[:{sub-discriminator}]
Rate limiting:    ratelimit:{org_id}:rpm:{unix_minute}
Auth token cache: auth:token:{sha256_hash}
Revocation set:   auth:revoked:{token_id}
Hot memory cache: {org_id}:hot_memories:{agent_id}
Memory object:    {org_id}:memory:{memory_id}
Directive cache:  {org_id}:directive:{agent_id}
Session state:    session:{session_id}:state
```

```go
// WRONG — no org_id; cross-tenant data collision
key := fmt.Sprintf("ratelimit:%d", unixMinute)
key := fmt.Sprintf("hot_memories:%s", agentID)

// RIGHT — org_id always present
key := fmt.Sprintf("ratelimit:%s:rpm:%d", orgID, unixMinute)
key := fmt.Sprintf("%s:hot_memories:%s", orgID, agentID)
```

## Every key must have an explicit TTL — no immortal keys

```go
// WRONG — key lives forever; data never expires; memory grows unbounded
client.Set(ctx, key, value, 0)

// RIGHT — explicit TTL from constants
const tokenCacheTTL = 30 * time.Second
client.Set(ctx, key, value, tokenCacheTTL)

// When using INCR (rate limiting): set TTL immediately after first increment
count, _ := client.Incr(ctx, key).Result()
if count == 1 {
    client.Expire(ctx, key, 90*time.Second)
}
```

## Fail open for rate limiting, fail closed for auth

```go
// Rate limiting — fail open (cost control, not security)
if err != nil {
    log.WarnCtx(ctx, "rate limit Redis error; failing open", "error", err)
    return ratelimit.Result{Allowed: true}, nil
}

// Auth cache — fail closed (security control)
// If Redis is down: call auth gRPC directly, do not assume token is valid
if err != nil {
    return authClient.ValidateToken(ctx, token)
}
```

## No raw JSON in Redis — always use a typed serialisation function

```go
// WRONG — raw JSON; schema changes silently break deserialization
client.Set(ctx, key, `{"org_id":"...","perms":123}`, ttl)
json.Unmarshal([]byte(val), &record)

// RIGHT — typed marshalling with version field for forward compat
type CachedToken struct {
    Version     int       `json:"v"` // bump when schema changes
    OrgID       uuid.UUID `json:"org_id"`
    Permissions int64     `json:"perms"`
    ExpiresAt   time.Time `json:"exp"`
}
data, _ := json.Marshal(CachedToken{Version: 1, ...})
client.Set(ctx, key, data, ttl)
```

## Pub/Sub channels — typed message envelopes

```go
// All pub/sub messages have a type discriminator for forward compatibility
type PubSubMessage struct {
    Type    string          `json:"type"`
    Payload json.RawMessage `json:"payload"`
}

// channel: directive_updates:{org_id}
type DirectiveUpdatedPayload struct {
    AgentID        uuid.UUID `json:"agent_id"`
    NewVersionID   uuid.UUID `json:"new_version_id"`
}
```
